               <msContents>
                  <summary>Psalter, ዳዊት፡, with Asmat Prayers and Varia</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="1r" to="68r"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT2701Dawit"/>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gə‘əz</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <watermark/>
                        </support>
                        <extent>
                           <measure unit="leaf"/>
                           <dimensions type="outer" unit="mm">
                              <height/>
                              <width/>
                              <depth/>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#130r"/> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#140r #140v"/> (tenth Biblical Canticle).</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d01"><locus target="#iiv(erso)"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1066DavidHarp"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d02">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#8r #15v #24v #35v #44r #50v #60v #73r #82r #88v #103r #114v #117v #124r #130v #144r #151v"/> (line of alternating red and black dots)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a01">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)"/>": Excerpt from <title type="complete" ref="LIT2940RepCh221"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a02">
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    <locus target="#167r"/>, column one and top of column two: Asmat prayer to bring a person back to their home
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a03">
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    <locus target="#167r"/>, column two: Asmat prayer against an enemy in the court
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a04">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#167v"/>: Excerpt from <title type="complete" ref="LIT2509Weddas"/> for Sunday, copied in a nineteenth- or twentieth-century hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a05">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#166r"/>: Note of ownership, with the original owner’s name erased.  A secondary owner is listed below, Ǝmäyät Žämanäš
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e01">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)"/>": Pen trials and notes, written upside down
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e02">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)"/>": Pen trials and notes, written upside down
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e03">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#55r #101r #162v"/>: badly faded seal
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e04">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#125r"/>: erased, illegible note
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e05">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#161v #162v"/>, bottom margins: inventory of cattle, written in a crude hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e06">
                    <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 25
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e07">
                    <desc>
                    Navigation system: red, yellow, and blue string is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#35 #44 #60 #88"/>;
                    red string is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#117 #124"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e08">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–9
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e09">
                    <desc>
                    Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters.  Occasionally, a second spiritual meaning is inserted by a later hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e10">
                    <desc>
                    Scribal intervention:
                    words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#2r #5r #6v #10v #12v"/>, etc.);
                    and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#78r #108v #110v #113v #135r"/>, etc.);
                    and in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted <locus target="#78v"/>, line 16);
                    erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#97v"/>); text has been removed (<locus target="#17r #62r #91v #101v #104r"/>, etc.).
                    </desc>
                    </item>
